headline: A Look At Rollins (ROL) Valuation After Its Q4 Revenue And EPS Miss
summary: Rollins (ROL) is in focus after its fourth quarter and full year 2025 results, where revenue and earnings per share came in below analyst forecasts, despite positive year-over-year growth across its key operating segments. See our latest analysis for Rollins. The immediate 13.6% drop in Rollins' share price after the earnings miss contrasts with its recent momentum, including a 7.5% 1 month share price return and 11.2% year to date share price return.
